        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 3:40PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 340 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Fritch, or 7 miles southwest of Borger, moving
northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sanford, Borger, Lake Meredith, and Fritch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
